column12: Briefing Sheet and Informed Consent FormHello, thank you for choosing to participate in our study.  We are a group of researchers from Temasek Polytechnic, Centre for Applied Behavioural & Social Sciences. Our survey aims to understand more about your traits, preferences, and thinking styles to design a machine-learning model to differentiate individuals for personalised behavioural interventions. You will be required to complete a survey that will take approximately 20 to 30 minutes. Please ensure that you are a current Temasek Polytechnic student. Please be assured that all responses provided by you in this survey will be kept anonymous and confidential, so we seek your cooperation to be as truthful as possible when providing your responses. Additionally, once you have completed the survey, you will receive a $5 NTUC voucher as a token of appreciation. Note that only participants who complete the full survey are entitled to the NTUC vouchers.Should you have any doubts at any point in time with regards to the study, you may email our Principal Investigator, Dr. Tan Wah Pheow (tan_wah_pheow@tp.edu.sg) for clarification.In order to proceed with the study, you will be required to tick the box below and in doing so, you will also be indicating your understanding of the following, and giving your consent to participate in the research study mentioned above. I understand that I have the right to:  1. Refuse participation if I do not wish to participate in this study, or feel uncomfortable with the topic of study.  2. Withdraw my participation at any point in time during the study without any explanation.  3. Have privacy of my personal data and any information that is collected in this study would not be identified.

column163: A bat and a ball cost $1.10 in total. The bat costs a dollar more than the ball. How much does the ball cost? ____ cents

column166: Jerry received both the 15th highest and the 15th lowest mark in the class. How many students are in the class? ______ students
column167: Q2
column168: If John can drink one barrel of water in 6 days, and Mary can drink one barrel of water in 12 days, how long would it take them to drink one barrel of water together?
column169: Q3
column170: A man buys a pig for $60, sells it for $70, buys it back for $80, and sells it finally for $90. How much has he made?
column171: Q4
column172: If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?
column173: Q5
column174: In a lake, there is a patch of lily pads. Every day, the patch doubles in size. If it takes 48 days for the patch to cover the entire lake, how long would it take for the patch to cover half of the lake?
column175: Q6
column176: Simon decided to invest $8,000 in the stock market one day early in 2008. Six months after he invested, on July 17, the stocks he had purchased were down 50%. Fortunately for Simon, from July 17 to October 17, the stocks he had purchased went up 75%. At this point, Simon has:
column177: Q7
column178: Thank you for your responses to the items in the previous pages. In this final section, we will be collecting some demographic information to better understand our participants. Please note that all personal information will be kept strictly confidential within the research team.
column186: Debriefing Sheet Thank you for participating in this study. Your participation is greatly appreciated, and the valuable data you have provided us will aid us in the investigation of our study. As mentioned earlier, the purpose of our survey aims to understand more about your traits to design a machine-learning model to differentiate individuals by traits for personalized behavioural interventions. Once again, we would like to assure you that your responses will be kept strictly confidential. The collected data will be kept securely and will only be accessible by our supervisor and the research team.   Should you face any discomfort or emotional distress arising from the survey, you may contact the following:  Student Support & Career Services Location: Temasek Polytechnic Care @ Blk 26B, Level 1, Unit 49  Telephone: 6780 5959 Opening Hours: 8.30 am to 5.30 pm (Mon to Fri). Closed on Sat, Sun & Public Holidays  Email: care@tp.edu.sg  We seek your kind understanding that you do not discuss any part of this research study with others (e.g., the purpose of the study, activities and interview questions) to have unbiased responses. We will also follow up with you regarding the $5 NTUC voucher in around 2 weeks' time via your TP email. Lastly, if you have any other queries regarding the study, or if you wish to know about the outcome of our study, please contact our Principal Investigator, Dr. Tan Wah Pheow (tan_wah_pheow@tp.edu.sg) for clarification. Once again, we would like to thank you for your participation and cooperation. Have a great day ahead.
